Aug 3 2009 	Cheap and cheerful	Having reada few of the reviews of the hotel two days before I travelled I was really quite worried about what I would find. On arrival, however, I was pleasantly surprised. Our room was on the ground floor and had two comfortable double beds, an adequately sized wet room with toilet, shower and wash basin, a kettle, hair-drier and TV. There was a good-sized wardrobe in which I quickly stored all our clothes (four of us there for five days) and there was still room to spare.The location was perfect. Just a two minute walk from the shops and restaurants and five minutes to Victoria station. All that and yet the street was very quiet; hardly any traffic and not much pedestrian noise. My only complaint was that we had to have the window open all the time due to the heat, though that was hardly their fault, it was a hot week. There was a fan in the room (not air-con) and combined they were sufficient to keep the room at an acceptable temperature.We only ventured down to breakfast on three mornings and found friendly staff and a small but servicable dining room. The toast and croissants were fine and the coffee was as coffee should be. There was a selection of cereals and fruit on offer and the lack of full english breakfast was made up for by the location of a fab cafe two minutes away (the name of which has, unfortunately slipped my mind).Overall we had a good week in London and would happily go back to the Caswell on our next visit.	
