May 9 2007 	got what I expected	Before travelling to London I had read many reviews telling that rooms in B&amp;Bs are rather small. That is why I wasn't surprised when I arrived at Caswell. My mother and I booked an en-suite room two months beforehand. The manager had let us have a look at our room before we paid the whole sum of money. As to the room itself, it was small, but quite cosy. It looked very similar to the one shown on the photos provided by the hotel. Beds and towels were clean. The shower was rather small but we coped quite ok. We enjoyed the breakfasts in spite of the fact that there wasn't much variety. There was a good range of cereals, jams and very tasty croissants and toasts. Also, what I liked a lot, was that we had a kettle, a tea pot and tea and coffee bags in our room. Speaking about the location, it was quite convenient. It took about ten minutes to reach Victoria station and several minutes to reach a bus stop. There was a reasonably priced supermarket in the area as well.All in all we were quite happy with our stay in this hotel.	
