May 27 2004	Nice try but no cigar	The Caswell Hotel is a double-edged sword. The downside is that the hotel is basically a dump. Filthy carpet, in need of paint, tiny (and I mean tiny) bathrooms, noisy plumbing all night long. The upside is that it's a great bargain -- we paid just 40 pounds per night for a double ensuite room. The breakfast was quite pleasant, and the 24 hour front desk staff were helpful. The Caswell makes a number of nice attempts (teacups in the room, a minibar, a safe in the room) to provide some comforts. The cleaning staff does what it can to keep the rooms clean and fresh, but unfortunately their resources are just too limited. My suggestion? Go for the Caswell if you're on a tight budget and don't mind a little grime. 	
